# Waterfall Pipeline

All waterfall state mutations live in `rules/waterfall.ts`. `GameBoard.tsx` only handles animation sequencing.

## Actions

| Action | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `APPLY_WATERFALL_EFFECTS` | Eternal relic effects, amulet temp mods, recycle restore, wraith enrage, hero skill reset |
| `APPLY_WATERFALL_DISCARD_EFFECTS` | Per-card discard effects: return-to-deck, bonus decay, gold loss, damage, equipment destruction, swarm infest |

## Flow

```
TRIGGER_WATERFALL (dungeon.ts)
  → emits waterfall:started, waterfall:dropPhase, waterfall:discardPhase, waterfall:dealPhase
  → GameBoard.tsx animates each phase via useGameEvent listeners
  → After animation completes: dispatch(APPLY_WATERFALL_EFFECTS)
  → For each discarded card: dispatch(APPLY_WATERFALL_DISCARD_EFFECTS)
  → emits waterfall:completed when done
```

## Rules

- **Never** put waterfall state mutations (relic effects, discard penalties, deck manipulation) in `GameBoard.tsx`
- `GameBoard.tsx` only sequences animations and dispatches actions at the right time
- Discard effects that modify the remaining deck use `nextRemainingDeck` parameter for in-place planning
- Waterfall discover (eternal relic) is triggered via `enqueuedActions` → `BEGIN_DISCOVER`
